Compiling the following code ([playground link](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=6915ae160a3039e40866627061fee11b)):

```rust
use std::future::Future;

trait MyFn<T> {
    type Output;

    fn call(&self, input: T) -> Self::Output;
}

// OK.
fn foo<T>(_: impl for<'a> MyFn<&'a T, Output = &'a T>) {}

// OK.
fn bar<T>(_: impl for<'a> MyFn<&'a T, Output = impl Future<Output = ()>>) {}

// Error.
fn foobar<T>(_: impl for<'a> MyFn<&'a T, Output = impl Future<Output = ()> + 'a>) {}
```

I got the this error:

```text
error[E0261]: use of undeclared lifetime name `'a`
  --> src/lib.rs:16:78
   |
16 | fn foobar<T>(_: impl for<'a> MyFn<&'a T, Output = impl Future<Output = ()> + 'a>) {}
   |           - help: consider introducing lifetime `'a` here: `'a,`             ^^ undeclared lifetime

For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0261`.
```
